metadata.name: Poseidon (Neptune)
metadata.description:
Poseidon is a Greek god of Olympus. 
(Known as Neptune in the Roman religion) 
Second son of the titans Cronus and Rhea. 
God of the sea and rivers. 
Creator of storms and floods and the bringer of earthquakes and destruction. 
Father and tamer of horses such as the Pegasus. 
Carrier of the trident.
